Package: shinyglass
Type: Package
Title: Apple-Inspired Liquid Glass Design for Shiny Applications
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Eric", "Anderson", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "eric.ray.anderson@gmail.com")
Description: Drop-in Apple-inspired Liquid Glass themes for 'shiny'.
    Call 'glass_theme()' and pass the result to 'fluidPage()',
    'navbarPage()', or any 'bslib'-aware page function to get
    translucent surfaces, backdrop blur, and system typography on
    Bootstrap components. Light and dark presets are included, with
    options for accent color, blur, and corner radius. See Apple's
    Liquid Glass design overview at
    <https://developer.apple.com/documentation/technologyoverviews/liquid-glass>.
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
URL: https://ericrayanderson.github.io/shinyglass/,
    https://github.com/ericrayanderson/shinyglass
BugReports: https://github.com/ericrayanderson/shinyglass/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    bslib (>= 0.5.0),
    htmltools (>= 0.5.0),
    sass (>= 0.4.0)
Suggests:
    DT,
    duckdb,
    ggplot2,
    querychat,
    shiny (>= 1.5.0),
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
